"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-06-21-paris-river-seine-olympics-pollution-limit-analysis\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France (AFP) - Paris' river Seine was too dirty when tested on June 16 to allow the Olympic triathlon and open-water swimming events to be held there, an analysis showed Friday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9979524944218232, \"rank\": 0.0019072167392134378, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 22, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999306768383, \"rank\": 6.932320075440546e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 35, \"end\": 40, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999979341810978, \"rank\": 1.898406020582049e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Samples from the Seine do not meet the standards we will have this summer\\\" for the river when the Olympic Games are held from July 26 to August 11, Paris region prefect Marc Guillaume said.\", \"from\": 186, \"to\": 376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 204, \"end\": 209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999979341810978, \"rank\": 1.898406020582049e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 335, \"end\": 340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999306768383, \"rank\": 6.932320075440546e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A weekly report published by the Paris region and mayor's office blamed unseasonal rainy weather for the high rates of two kinds of faecal bacteria including E. Coli in the waterway.\", \"from\": 378, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 411, \"end\": 416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999306768383, \"rank\": 6.932320075440546e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Water quality remains degraded due to\\u2026 rain, high flow, little sunshine (and) temperatures below seasonal norms,\\\" it said.\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 685, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Results posted online showed concentration of E. Coli was higher than the recommended limit in four locations of the river for practically all of the week of June 10 to 16.\", \"from\": 687, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine is supposed to host both the Olympics opening ceremony as well as open-water events during the Games.\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 865, \"end\": 870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999979341810978, \"rank\": 1.898406020582049e-06, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Paris has been holding its breath hoping for the river to be clean enough.\", \"from\": 974, \"to\": 1052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 978, \"end\": 983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999306768383, \"rank\": 6.932320075440546e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In August last year, the swimming marathon test events were cancelled because the water was too dirty, as were the swimming legs on two of the four days of triathlon and para-triathlon tests.\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1245, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If the river is too polluted when the Olympics kick off, the plan B is to postpone open-water swimming events for a few days - not to move them to a new location.\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1422, \"entities\": []}]}"